Movement has been restricted for the December 5 Cross River North Senatorial by-election. A statement by the police spokesman, Irene Ugbo, said Commissioner of Police Abdulkadir Jimoh banned movement of persons, groups and motorists within the five local government areas comprising the senatorial district where the election will hold. The curfew holds from 6am to 6pm, but exempts those on essential duties who must however bear identification tags.